# =================
# DATABASE CONFIGURATION
# =================
# PostgreSQL connection string from Supabase project
# 
# IMPORTANT: Supabase Database URL Format
# ---------------------------------------------
# Supabase provides PostgreSQL URLs in the standard format:
#   postgresql://postgres:[PASSWORD]@db.[PROJECT_REF].supabase.co:5432/postgres
# 
# The application automatically handles this conversion during startup through a custom
# database configuration class. The transformation process:
# 1. Reads the DATABASE_URL environment variable from Supabase
# 2. Detects if the URL starts with "postgresql://" 
# 3. Automatically prepends "jdbc:" to create the proper JDBC connection string
# 4. Configures the Spring Boot DataSource with the converted URL
#
# This ensures seamless integration between Supabase database and Spring Boot's
# JDBC connectivity requirements without manual URL modification.
#
# Example DATABASE_URL (from Supabase Dashboard → Database → Connection string):
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:YOUR_PASSWORD@db.PROJECT_REF.supabase.co:5432/postgres

